(c) Notwithstanding ARTICLE VIII , the license granted to the SpinCo Group under Section 3.03(a) may continue unless explicitly terminated upon any of the following events:

(i) If a member of the SpinCo Group grants, transfers, licenses, or otherwise conveys any rights in or to the Honeywell Content to any third party;

(ii) In instances where:
   (x) Any member of the SpinCo Group sells less than all or substantially all of its ownership interests, whether individually or through a series of unrelated transactions, to one or more third parties;
   (y) Any direct or indirect acquisition, consolidation, or merger occurs involving any member of the SpinCo Group with, by, or into any third party;
   (z) A spin-off, public offering, or other corporate reorganization transpires in which less than fifty percent (50%) of a member of the SpinCo Group's voting power, shares, or equity is transferred to one or more third parties through a merger, consolidation, tender offer, or similar transaction.

This revised clause weakens the obligation by providing the SpinCo Group with the opportunity to maintain the license even when any of the specified events occur, unless explicitly terminated.
